kept on telling myself

00:02:26.450 --> 00:02:28.040 align:middle line:84%
is, how did this
happen, how am I

00:02:28.040 --> 00:02:32.220 align:middle line:84%
going to get out of this,
what am I going to do.

00:02:32.220 --> 00:02:34.170 align:middle line:90%
And I felt really helpless.

00:02:34.170 --> 00:02:39.020 align:middle line:84%
And for a really brief moment,
I wanted to end it all.

00:02:39.020 --> 00:02:43.070 align:middle line:84%
And not because I wanted to end
it all like really end it all,

00:02:43.070 --> 00:02:45.800 align:middle line:90%
I just wanted the pain to stop.

00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:48.950 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know how to
make that pain stop.

00:02:48.950 --> 00:02:50.480 align:middle line:84%
And so what I
allowed myself to do,

00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:54.508 align:middle line:84%
is I just allowed myself
to just cry it all out.

00:02:54.508 --> 00:02:57.050 align:middle line:84%
You know, sometimes when we're
going through a difficult time

00:02:57.050 --> 00:02:59.630 align:middle line:84%
and we want to cry or
we feel like crying,

00:02:59.630 --> 00:03:03.170 align:middle line:84%
we do everything possible to not
do that and distract ourselves.

00:03:03.170 --> 00:03:06.110 align:middle line:84%
