something bad is happening.

00:37:25.902 --> 00:37:28.235 align:middle line:84%
But if it's 20 years later,
then that's not a good thing

00:37:28.235 --> 00:37:29.402 align:middle line:90%
and you're doing this wrong.

00:37:29.402 --> 00:37:30.740 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:37:30.740 --> 00:37:33.160 align:middle line:84%
It's OK to feel bad when
something bad's happening.

00:37:33.160 --> 00:37:36.580 align:middle line:84%
You can actually allow yourself
to be a victim, because you're

00:37:36.580 --> 00:37:38.118 align:middle line:90%
doing it consciously now.

00:37:38.118 --> 00:37:39.160 align:middle line:90%
It's like, you know what?

00:37:39.160 --> 00:37:41.080 align:middle line:84%
I just broke up
with my boyfriend,

00:37:41.080 --> 00:37:43.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm really, really
sad right now.

00:37:43.120 --> 00:37:45.550 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have to
buck up and be strong

00:37:45.550 --> 00:37:47.790 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to, I
could do this, la-la-la.

00:37:47.790 --> 00:37:48.590 align:middle line:90%
You know what?

00:37:48.590 --> 00:37:51.590 align:middle line:84%
My heart is ripped
open, I'm broken open.

00:37:51.590 --> 00:37:53.090 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to cry
right now and allow

00:37:53.090 --> 00:37:55.437 align:middle line:90%
myself to play the victim.

00:37:55.437 --> 00:37:57.020 align:middle line:84%
You're like giving
yourself permission

00:37:57.020 --> 00:37:58.850 align:middle line:90%
to feel what you're feeling.

00:37:58.850 --> 00:38:00.920 align:middle line:84%
What's amazing
with doing that, is

00:38:00.920 --> 00:38:05.355 align:middle line:84%
that you're allowing yourself
to release what, you're human.

00:38:05.355 --> 00:38:07.730 align:middle line:84%
Of course you're going to have
times when you want to cry

00:38:07.730 --> 00:38:09.380 align:middle line:90%
and you want to let it out.

00:38:09.380 --> 00:38:11.180 align:middle line:84%
You don't always
have to be strong,

00:38:11.180 --> 00:38:14.060 align:middle line:84%
and you don't always
have to be perfect.

00:38:14.060 --> 00:38:16.850 align:middle line:84%
So you allow yourself
to release it.

00:38:16.850 --> 00:38:18.980 align:middle line:84%
And just that
release immediately

00:38:18.980 --> 00:38:20.810 align:middle line:90%
makes you feel better.

00:38:20.810 --> 00:38:26.630 align:middle line:84%
And so I actually tell people,
listen, even though all that

00:38:26.630 --> 00:38:31.010 align:middle line:84%
happened, after that and more
recently, my mom passed away.

00:38:31.010 --> 00:38:32.950 align:middle line:84%
And that honestly,
everything that happened,

00:38:32.950 --> 00:38:33.950 align:middle line:90%
this is the ironic part.

00:38:33.950 --> 00:38:36.253 align:middle line:84%
Everything is relative,
because all that.

00:38:36.253 --> 00:38:37.670 align:middle line:84%
I lost my home due
to foreclosure,

00:38:37.670 --> 00:38:40.550 align:middle line:84%
I was $124,000 in debt,
my ex was an alcoholic,

00:38:40.550 --> 00:38:43.790 align:middle line:84%
relationship broke up, I had
serious blood clot health

00:38:43.790 --> 00:38:44.590 align:middle line:90%
issues.

00:38:44.590 --> 00:38:46.798 align:middle line:84%
Oh my god, that's the worst
thing that ever happened.

00:38:46.798 --> 00:38:49.760 align:middle line:84%
Until my mom got cancer
and was really sick

00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:52.280 align:middle line:84%
and I watched her deteriorate
in front of my eyes

00:38:52.280 --> 00:38:56.600 align:middle line:84%
and die in front of me and I
watch her take her last breath.

00:38:56.600 --> 00:38:58.940 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden, that
stuff, that's a joke.

00:38:58.940 --> 00:39:01.780 align:middle line:90%


00:39:01.780 --> 00:39:03.350 align:middle line:90%
So it's all relative.

00:39:03.350 --> 00:39:07.390 align:middle line:84%
And so the reason I'm mentioning
that is that it just occurred

00:39:07.390 --> 00:39:09.370 align:middle line:84%
to me, especially when
my mom passed away,

00:39:09.370 --> 00:39:11.230 align:middle line:84%
is what's really
important in life,

00:39:11.230 --> 00:39:15.220 align:middle line:84%
and how we put so much
emphasis on all these things

00:39:15.220 --> 00:39:17.200 align:middle line:84%
until something
really big happens.

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:19.040 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
that's not important.

00:39:19.040 --> 00:39:21.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm telling you, when
my mom was hospitalized.

00:39:21.340 --> 00:39:24.370 align:middle line:84%
Before she passed away, she
was hospitalized for six weeks.

00:39:24.370 --> 00:39:26.830 align:middle line:84%
Before that, I was
tired, exhausted

00:39:26.830 --> 00:39:27.870 align:middle line:90%
with work and all that.

00:39:27.870 --> 00:39:29.620 align:middle line:84%
I needed to take time
off, but I couldn't,

00:39:29.620 --> 00:39:31.610 align:middle line:90%
because I'm way too busy.

00:39:31.610 --> 00:39:33.260 align:middle line:84%
I've got too much
stuff going on.

00:39:33.260 --> 00:39:35.380 align:middle line:84%
Like, I just can't
take time off.

00:39:35.380 --> 00:39:37.630 align:middle line:84%
Soon as my mom was hospitalized,
I all of a sudden I'm

00:39:37.630 --> 00:39:40.420 align:middle line:90%
out for over six weeks.

00:39:40.420 --> 00:39:42.340 align:middle line:90%
Where did that come from?

00:39:42.340 --> 00:39:44.650 align:middle line:84%
It's because I got my
priorities straight.

00:39:44.650 --> 00:39:51.130 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I'm saying
that, is that in the end,

00:39:51.130 --> 00:39:54.130 align:middle line:84%
yes, there'll be times that
you will play the victim,

00:39:54.130 --> 00:39:56.950 align:middle line:84%
but that's not
necessarily a bad thing.

00:39:56.950 --> 00:39:59.230 align:middle line:84%
Because sometimes
things really do

00:39:59.230 --> 00:40:01.450 align:middle line:90%
happen that make you feel bad.

00:40:01.450 --> 00:40:04.300 align:middle line:84%
And don't let
anyone ever tell you

00:40:04.300 --> 00:40:05.500 align:middle line:90%
that you shouldn't feel bad.

00:40:05.500 --> 00:40:07.917 align:middle line:84%
No one should be telling you
how you should feel any time.

00:40:07.917 --> 00:40:10.660 align:middle line:84%
You can bounce
back, and you will.

00:40:10.660 --> 00:40:12.340 align:middle line:90%
It's how quickly you'll do it.

00:40:12.340 --> 00:40:15.200 align:middle line:84%
But it's OK to feel
bad in that moment.

00:40:15.200 --> 00:40:18.250 align:middle line:84%
And so I don't know
how comfortable I feel,

00:40:18.250 --> 00:40:21.360 align:middle line:84%
like even that
whole word, victim.

00:40:21.360 --> 00:40:24.100 align:middle line:84%
Like, it's not
victim, it's life.

00:40:24.100 --> 00:40:26.590 align:middle line:90%
Life is life and things happen.

00:40:26.590 --> 00:40:29.080 align:middle line:84%
Good things happen,
bad things happen.

00:40:29.080 --> 00:40:30.910 align:middle line:90%
My mom used to always say this.

00:40:30.910 --> 00:40:34.570 align:middle line:90%
Sonia, life is like a staircase.

00:40:34.570 --> 00:40:38.283 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes you go up and
sometimes you go down.

00:40:38.283 --> 00:40:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And when you go
down and you don't

00:40:39.700 --> 00:40:43.450 align:middle line:84%
feel good, allow it, release
it, feel it at a deep level.

00:40:43.450 --> 00:40:45.480 align:middle line:84%
I did that when my
mom was hospitalized.

00:40:45.480 --> 00:40:48.082 align:middle line:84%
Seriously, I was crying
every day in the hospital.

00:40:48.082 --> 00:40:49.165 align:middle line:90%
I didn't care where I was.

00:40:49.165 --> 00:40:51.740 align:middle line:84%
I was waiting for the elevator
in the hospital, I was crying.

00:40:51.740 --> 00:40:53.073 align:middle line:90%
I was in the room, I was crying.

00:40:53.073 --> 00:40:55.430 align:middle line:84%
The nurse and doctor
there, I was crying.

00:40:55.430 --> 00:40:56.890 align:middle line:90%
I never apologized ever.

00:40:56.890 --> 00:40:57.690 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:40:57.690 --> 00:41:01.330 align:middle line:84%
Because that's what I
felt. My mom's dying.

00:41:01.330 --> 00:41:05.710 align:middle line:84%
So I feel sad and I'm going
to cry, and I'll be OK.

00:41:05.710 --> 00:41:08.690 align:middle line:90%


00:41:08.690 --> 00:41:09.490 align:middle line:90%
I'll be OK.

00:41:09.490 --> 00:41:11.778 align:middle line:84%
But this is how
I feel right now.

00:41:11.778 --> 00:41:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And the good news is,
I had the tools to be

00:41:13.570 --> 00:41:15.620 align:middle line:90%
able to bounce back after that.

00:41:15.620 --> 00:41:18.732 align:middle line:84%
But I think playing
the victim to me really

00:41:18.732 --> 00:41:21.190 align:middle line:84%
means like it's 20 years later
and you're still complaining

00:41:21.190 --> 00:41:22.940 align:middle line:84%
about something that
happened 20 years ago

00:41:22.940 --> 00:41:24.850 align:middle line:84%
and you're just
not letting it go.

00:41:24.850 --> 00:41:27.130 align:middle line:84%
And that is actually a
huge part, by the way,

00:41:27.130 --> 00:41:31.190 align:middle line:90%
of step number three.

00:41:31.190 --> 00:41:33.180 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to know what
step number three is?

00:41:33.180 --> 00:41:34.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course.

00:41:34.940 --> 00:41:37.050 align:middle line:84%
>> And I love breaking
it into three steps,

00:41:37.050 --> 00:41:39.940 align:middle line:84%
just so it's so much
easier to grasp.

00:41:39.940 --> 00:41:43.900 align:middle line:84%
Step number three is elevating
your vibrational frequency

00:41:43.900 --> 00:41:49.570 align:middle line:84%
to a state of love,
peace, joy and gratitude.

00:41:49.570 --> 00:41:52.220 align:middle line:84%
Once you get yourself to a
state of love, peace, joy

00:41:52.220 --> 00:41:56.030 align:middle line:84%
and gratitude, everything
will shift in your life.

00:41:56.030 --> 00:41:57.190 align:middle line:90%
Everything.

00:41:57.190 --> 00:41:59.830 align:middle line:84%
Now whether you believe
in the Law of Attraction

00:41:59.830 --> 00:42:01.610 align:middle line:84%
or you don't, it
doesn't really matter.

00:42:01.610 --> 00:42:03.010 align:middle line:90%
Think about it.

00:42:03.010 --> 00:42:05.480 align:middle line:84%
If you get yourself to a
state of love, peace, joy

00:42:05.480 --> 00:42:09.100 align:middle line:84%
and gratitude, how
would you feel?

00:42:09.100 --> 00:42:11.110 align:middle line:90%
How would you like your life?

00:42:11.110 --> 00:42:12.560 align:middle line:90%
It would be great.

00:42:12.560 --> 00:42:14.070 align:middle line:90%
Doesn't matter what you believe.

00:42:14.070 --> 00:42:15.820 align:middle line:84%
But I'm telling you,
once you get yourself

00:42:15.820 --> 00:42:17.840 align:middle line:84%
to a state of love,
peace, joy and gratitude,

00:42:17.840 --> 00:42:20.920 align:middle line:84%
which is the highest vibrational
frequency, especially love

00:42:20.920 --> 00:42:22.870 align:middle line:84%
and peace, really
powerful, and you

00:42:22.870 --> 00:42:25.780 align:middle line:84%
do the work to be
able to get to that,

00:42:25.780 --> 00:42:27.820 align:middle line:84%
everything will be
OK in your life,

00:42:27.820 --> 00:42:32.230 align:middle line:84%
even when something quote
unquote, bad, happens.

00:42:32.230 --> 00:42:36.670 align:middle line:84%
And so you'll start attracting
more positive people, things,

00:42:36.670 --> 00:42:38.080 align:middle line:90%
situations in your life.

00:42:38.080 --> 00:42:38.880 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:42:38.880 --> 00:42:40.768 align:middle line:90%
Because that's who you're being.

00:42:40.768 --> 00:42:43.347 align:middle line:84%
You're being love,
peace, joy and gratitude.

00:42:43.347 --> 00:42:45.430 align:middle line:84%
That is what you will
attract back into your life.

00:42:45.430 --> 00:42:48.658 align:middle line:84%
When you're being negative,
angry, resentful, all that,

00:42:48.658 --> 00:42:50.200 align:middle line:84%
you're going to
attract more of that.

00:42:50.200 --> 00:42:50.530 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:42:50.530 --> 00:42:52.780 align:middle line:84%
Because that's what you're
focusing on and that's what

00:42:52.780 --> 00:42:54.010 align:middle line:90%
you're going to see.

00:42:54.010 --> 00:42:56.260 align:middle line:90%
Remember all those open doors?

00:42:56.260 --> 00:42:57.072 align:middle line:90%
They're not there.

00:42:57.072 --> 00:42:59.530 align:middle line:84%
When you're in love, peace,
joy and gratitude, you're like,

00:42:59.530 --> 00:43:01.100 align:middle line:84%
I've never seen so
many open doors.

00:43:01.100 --> 00:43:03.235 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know which
one to go through, wow!

00:43:03.235 --> 00:43:05.740 align:middle line:90%


00:43:05.740 --> 00:43:09.220 align:middle line:84%
And so how do you get to a
state of love, peace, joy

00:43:09.220 --> 00:43:12.160 align:middle line:84%
and gratitude is the number one
question people always ask me.

00:43:12.160 --> 00:43:14.080 align:middle line:90%
And there's many ways.

00:43:14.080 --> 00:43:16.340 align:middle line:84%
There are many ways
that you can do it.

00:43:16.340 --> 00:43:21.130 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things,
I'm going to give you

00:43:21.130 --> 00:43:23.140 align:middle line:90%
a few ways of doing it.

00:43:23.140 --> 00:43:26.620 align:middle line:84%
And probably all these
things you should do.

00:43:26.620 --> 00:43:30.285 align:middle line:90%
Let go of the negative past.

00:43:30.285 --> 00:43:32.410 align:middle line:84%
Because when you're holding
onto the negative past,

00:43:32.410 --> 00:43:34.922 align:middle line:84%
the negative things that
happened to you in the past,

00:43:34.922 --> 00:43:36.880 align:middle line:84%
not only are you bringing
it into your present,

00:43:36.880 --> 00:43:39.100 align:middle line:84%
but you're affecting
your future.

00:43:39.100 --> 00:43:42.190 align:middle line:84%
Because every decision you
make, how you see things,

00:43:42.190 --> 00:43:45.580 align:middle line:84%
your perception, you're holding
onto something from the past,

00:43:45.580 --> 00:43:48.580 align:middle line:90%
so it's very negative.

00:43:48.580 --> 00:43:51.490 align:middle line:84%
And so if you don't let
go of the negative past,

00:43:51.490 --> 00:43:53.650 align:middle line:84%
it will be difficult
to transform

00:43:53.650 --> 00:43:56.770 align:middle line:90%
your life going forward.

00:43:56.770 --> 00:43:59.780 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people say,
well, how do we do that?

00:43:59.780 --> 00:44:09.580 align:middle line:84%
Well, one great way is to think
of the past as no longer real.

00:44:09.580 --> 00:44:13.090 align:middle line:84%
Because the reality is,
the past doesn't exist.

00:44:13.090 --> 00:44:15.790 align:middle line:90%
And a lot of people argue that.

00:44:15.790 --> 00:44:17.267 align:middle line:90%
And it doesn't exist.

00:44:17.267 --> 00:44:18.100 align:middle line:90%
Where does it exist?

00:44:18.100 --> 00:44:19.030 align:middle line:90%
Show it to me.

00:44:19.030 --> 00:44:20.590 align:middle line:84%
Where does it,
where does it exist?

00:44:20.590 --> 00:44:21.680 align:middle line:90%
Is it this?

00:44:21.680 --> 00:44:22.480 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't exist.

00:44:22.480 --> 00:44:26.230 align:middle line:84%
The only place it exists
is this thing again!

00:44:26.230 --> 00:44:29.410 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't exist.

00:44:29.410 --> 00:44:34.700 align:middle line:84%
And so the past, we're keeping
the past alive by our thoughts.

00:44:34.700 --> 00:44:36.930 align:middle line:84%
So the past are
really just thoughts.

00:44:36.930 --> 00:44:37.730 align:middle line:90%
They don't exist.

00:44:37.730 --> 00:44:41.560 align:middle line:84%
Yes, it happened, but it's
like reading a history book.

00:44:41.560 --> 00:44:44.360 align:middle line:84%
World War I happened,
World War II happened,

00:44:44.360 --> 00:44:47.350 align:middle line:84%
Sonia's ex was an
alcoholic and it was

00:44:47.350 --> 00:44:50.530 align:middle line:90%
a miserable time in her life.

00:44:50.530 --> 00:44:55.630 align:middle line:84%
And so the past doesn't really
exist when you really think

00:44:55.630 --> 00:44:57.310 align:middle line:90%
about it, except as a thought.

00:44:57.310 --> 00:45:00.490 align:middle line:84%
So if you could shift that
thought, you can let it go.

00:45:00.490 --> 00:45:04.240 align:middle line:84%
Hold on to those positive
experiences over time.

00:45:04.240 --> 00:45:06.670 align:middle line:90%
The crazy part is this.

00:45:06.670 --> 00:45:10.870 align:middle line:84%
Is that the future
doesn't exist either.

00:45:10.870 --> 00:45:15.580 align:middle line:90%
So the future is also a thought.

00:45:15.580 --> 00:45:17.860 align:middle line:90%
Think about it.

00:45:17.860 --> 00:45:20.200 align:middle line:84%
When you're thinking about
the future, you're thinking.

00:45:20.200 --> 00:45:21.225 align:middle line:90%
It's not real.

00:45:21.225 --> 00:45:23.350 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean you don't
think about the future,

00:45:23.350 --> 00:45:24.290 align:middle line:90%
you don't plan for the future.

00:45:24.290 --> 00:45:25.090 align:middle line:90%
Of course, you do.

00:45:25.090 --> 00:45:25.930 align:middle line:90%
But think about it.

00:45:25.930 --> 00:45:27.832 align:middle line:90%
The future doesn't exist either.

00:45:27.832 --> 00:45:29.290 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to
know that anytime

00:45:29.290 --> 00:45:32.260 align:middle line:84%
you're feeling stressed
or angry or worried,

00:45:32.260 --> 00:45:36.400 align:middle line:84%
chances are you were either,
all those negative feelings,

00:45:36.400 --> 00:45:38.608 align:middle line:84%
you're either focusing on
what happened in the past

00:45:38.608 --> 00:45:40.900 align:middle line:84%
or you're worrying about
what's going on in the future.

00:45:40.900 --> 00:45:42.755 align:middle line:90%
You're not in the present.

00:45:42.755 --> 00:45:44.380 align:middle line:84%
So as soon as you
become aware of that,

00:45:44.380 --> 00:45:46.918 align:middle line:84%
that immediately makes
everything better.

00:45:46.918 --> 00:45:48.460 align:middle line:84%
Because as soon as
you bring yourself

00:45:48.460 --> 00:45:51.730 align:middle line:84%
into this present moment,
which is my point here,

00:45:51.730 --> 00:45:55.240 align:middle line:84%
is that the past doesn't exist,
the future doesn't exist,

00:45:55.240 --> 00:45:58.180 align:middle line:84%
the only thing that exists
is this moment right now.

00:45:58.180 --> 00:46:00.070 align:middle line:84%
This conversation
we're having right

00:46:00.070 --> 00:46:04.270 align:middle line:84%
now is all that exists
in this exact moment.

00:46:04.270 --> 00:46:06.640 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't mean you
don't plan for the future.

00:46:06.640 --> 00:46:10.900 align:middle line:84%
Because remember, while you're
planning, and once it arrives,

00:46:10.900 --> 00:46:14.650 align:middle line:84%
it's not the future anymore,
it's the present again.

00:46:14.650 --> 00:46:16.930 align:middle line:90%
This is all there is.

00:46:16.930 --> 00:46:20.088 align:middle line:84%
And so the reason
I'm mentioning that,

00:46:20.088 --> 00:46:21.880 align:middle line:84%
is as soon as you let
go of the past, which

00:46:21.880 --> 00:46:25.400 align:middle line:84%
is all negative energy,
then you can get yourself

00:46:25.400 --> 00:46:27.400 align:middle line:84%
to that state of love,
peace, joy and gratitude,

00:46:27.400 --> 00:46:29.620 align:middle line:84%
because it's not
holding you back.

00:46:29.620 --> 00:46:32.300 align:middle line:90%
Forgiveness is another thing.

00:46:32.300 --> 00:46:35.120 align:middle line:84%
But of course, forgiveness has
everything to do with your past

00:46:35.120 --> 00:46:35.920 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:46:35.920 --> 00:46:37.795 align:middle line:84%
It's based on something
that happened to you,

