00:55:47.310 --> 00:55:49.140 align:middle line:90%
This is a perfect example.

00:55:49.140 --> 00:55:53.250 align:middle line:84%
So when the police officer came
and I rolled down my window

00:55:53.250 --> 00:55:55.860 align:middle line:84%
and then I have already have
my paperwork, insurance,

00:55:55.860 --> 00:55:58.815 align:middle line:84%
my driver's license,
and he looks down

00:55:58.815 --> 00:56:00.690 align:middle line:84%
and I go, here you go,
I know I was speeding.

00:56:00.690 --> 00:56:03.750 align:middle line:90%


00:56:03.750 --> 00:56:04.890 align:middle line:90%
I just admitted it.

00:56:04.890 --> 00:56:05.700 align:middle line:90%
Like who does that?

00:56:05.700 --> 00:56:06.630 align:middle line:90%
Nobody does that.

00:56:06.630 --> 00:56:08.700 align:middle line:84%
I know I was
speeding, here you go.

00:56:08.700 --> 00:56:10.200 align:middle line:90%
And he's like, what?

00:56:10.200 --> 00:56:12.940 align:middle line:90%
I said, I know I was speeding.

00:56:12.940 --> 00:56:16.020 align:middle line:90%
He was like, oh, OK.

00:56:16.020 --> 00:56:17.880 align:middle line:90%
And he goes, I'll be back.

00:56:17.880 --> 00:56:19.620 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, OK.

00:56:19.620 --> 00:56:20.550 align:middle line:90%
That was it.

00:56:20.550 --> 00:56:22.560 align:middle line:84%
And of course, at the back of
my mind I was thinking, well,

00:56:22.560 --> 00:56:24.570 align:middle line:84%
should I have said, oh,
I'm sorry officer, and all

00:56:24.570 --> 00:56:25.695 align:middle line:90%
the whole story in my head.

00:56:25.695 --> 00:56:28.230 align:middle line:84%
I go, no, that's
all I needed to say.

00:56:28.230 --> 00:56:30.940 align:middle line:84%
I was speeding, and
basically, I deserve this.

00:56:30.940 --> 00:56:32.730 align:middle line:84%
And then he goes
back to the car.

00:56:32.730 --> 00:56:34.820 align:middle line:84%
He comes back five minutes
later and he goes, OK,

00:56:34.820 --> 00:56:38.880 align:middle line:84%
just to let you know, I reduced
it like you were going 115.

00:56:38.880 --> 00:56:40.080 align:middle line:90%
So no demerit points.

00:56:40.080 --> 00:56:42.920 align:middle line:84%
And it's like $60
ticket, here you go.

00:56:42.920 --> 00:56:46.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, thank you, officer,
I really appreciate it.

00:56:46.620 --> 00:56:47.820 align:middle line:90%
And I took off.

00:56:47.820 --> 00:56:50.250 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't, I wasn't
upset, I wasn't angry,

00:56:50.250 --> 00:56:51.930 align:middle line:90%
there was no negativity.

00:56:51.930 --> 00:56:54.450 align:middle line:84%
And if it were many years
before, I'd probably

00:56:54.450 --> 00:56:58.080 align:middle line:84%
be crying, oh no, officer, oh,
my goodness, I can't believe,

00:56:58.080 --> 00:56:59.280 align:middle line:90%
I'm so sorry.

00:56:59.280 --> 00:57:01.030 align:middle line:84%
And oh, now I'm
going to lose points.

00:57:01.030 --> 00:57:03.000 align:middle line:84%
And oh my god, my
insurance, and oh, how much

00:57:03.000 --> 00:57:04.125 align:middle line:90%
is this ticket going to be?

00:57:04.125 --> 00:57:05.832 align:middle line:84%
Like, all this
negativity and who

00:57:05.832 --> 00:57:07.290 align:middle line:84%
knows how it would
have turned out.

00:57:07.290 --> 00:57:09.600 align:middle line:84%
One, I would have
definitely felt worse.

00:57:09.600 --> 00:57:12.210 align:middle line:84%
So the reason I'm
saying that, is

00:57:12.210 --> 00:57:15.630 align:middle line:84%
that's the easiest
way to really bounce

00:57:15.630 --> 00:57:19.560 align:middle line:84%
back immediately from
a being standpoint,

00:57:19.560 --> 00:57:23.490 align:middle line:84%
is just stop resisting
what's going on in your life.

00:57:23.490 --> 00:57:25.230 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we have
five different things,

00:57:25.230 --> 00:57:28.360 align:middle line:84%
and we feel like
everything's falling apart.

00:57:28.360 --> 00:57:31.140 align:middle line:84%
And so a great way
to stop resisting,

00:57:31.140 --> 00:57:34.695 align:middle line:84%
is just ask yourself
this question.

00:57:34.695 --> 00:57:37.350 align:middle line:90%


00:57:37.350 --> 00:57:42.780 align:middle line:84%
What problems do I have right
now right in this moment?

00:57:42.780 --> 00:57:45.240 align:middle line:84%
As you're watching
this, listening

00:57:45.240 --> 00:57:49.320 align:middle line:84%
to this, what problems
do you have right now?

00:57:49.320 --> 00:57:51.240 align:middle line:90%
Like this second.

00:57:51.240 --> 00:57:55.020 align:middle line:84%
Now unless a bear is
attacking you right now,

00:57:55.020 --> 00:57:59.100 align:middle line:84%
which is a problem, you wouldn't
be watching this right now.

00:57:59.100 --> 00:58:01.988 align:middle line:84%
You don't have any
problems right now.

00:58:01.988 --> 00:58:04.530 align:middle line:10%
And the reason I'm saying that,
is because you bring yourself

00:58:04.530 --> 00:58:07.050 align:middle line:10%
into the present.

00:58:07.050 --> 00:58:09.810 align:middle line:84%
And once you do that, then
just enjoy life right now.

00:58:09.810 --> 00:58:11.130 align:middle line:90%
Can you just let it go?

00:58:11.130 --> 00:58:12.120 align:middle line:90%
Just temporarily.

00:58:12.120 --> 00:58:15.063 align:middle line:90%
10 minutes, 10 hours, whatever.

00:58:15.063 --> 00:58:16.980 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you just enjoy
this moment right now

00:58:16.980 --> 00:58:18.360 align:middle line:84%
and allow yourself
to enjoy life?

00:58:18.360 --> 00:58:21.045 align:middle line:84%
You could worry about
your problems later.

00:58:21.045 --> 00:58:23.377 align:middle line:90%


00:58:23.377 --> 00:58:24.460 align:middle line:90%
And you ask that question.

00:58:24.460 --> 00:58:26.343 align:middle line:84%
What problems do I
have right this second?

00:58:26.343 --> 00:58:27.760 align:middle line:84%
Because what happens
is, this mind

00:58:27.760 --> 00:58:29.560 align:middle line:84%
is going on and on
and on and on and on,

00:58:29.560 --> 00:58:31.060 align:middle line:84%
and oh my god, I can't
believe that happened,

00:58:31.060 --> 00:58:33.393 align:middle line:84%
oh my goodness, oh, my god,
I've got all these problems.

00:58:33.393 --> 00:58:35.260 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to
get out of debt?

00:58:35.260 --> 00:58:37.430 align:middle line:84%
My so-and-so is sick, I've
got these health issues.

00:58:37.430 --> 00:58:39.305 align:middle line:84%
What am I going to do,
what am I going to do?

00:58:39.305 --> 00:58:41.680 align:middle line:90%
Future, past.

00:58:41.680 --> 00:58:45.310 align:middle line:84%
And meanwhile, what
we have right now,

00:58:45.310 --> 00:58:48.140 align:middle line:84%
the only thing that counts
right now is the present moment.

00:58:48.140 --> 00:58:49.100 align:middle line:90%
This is our life.

00:58:49.100 --> 00:58:50.308 align:middle line:90%
Everything else is a thought.

00:58:50.308 --> 00:58:52.590 align:middle line:90%


00:58:52.590 --> 00:58:55.120 align:middle line:84%
So you just bring yourself
to this present moment,

00:58:55.120 --> 00:58:58.080 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, yes, I have
issues and problems and things

00:58:58.080 --> 00:58:59.640 align:middle line:90%
I need to resolve.

00:58:59.640 --> 00:59:01.150 align:middle line:84%
But right now, I
want to feel good,

00:59:01.150 --> 00:59:02.817 align:middle line:84%
so I'm not going
to focus on that.

00:59:02.817 --> 00:59:04.650 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to focus on
this moment right now.

00:59:04.650 --> 00:59:06.700 align:middle line:84%
What problems do I
have right this second?

00:59:06.700 --> 00:59:07.500 align:middle line:90%
None.

00:59:07.500 --> 00:59:09.000 align:middle line:84%
That's a great way to
fall asleep at night.

00:59:09.000 --> 00:59:10.650 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes at night when
you're stressed out,

00:59:10.650 --> 00:59:12.690 align:middle line:84%
you can't sleep because
you got all these problems.

00:59:12.690 --> 00:59:13.740 align:middle line:90%
Ask yourself that question.

00:59:13.740 --> 00:59:16.170 align:middle line:84%
What problems do I have right
now as I'm lying in my bed,

00:59:16.170 --> 00:59:20.040 align:middle line:84%
cozy, under the covers,
nice and quiet and dark?

00:59:20.040 --> 00:59:22.350 align:middle line:90%
I have a roof over my head.

00:59:22.350 --> 00:59:26.435 align:middle line:84%
I'm, I don't have any
problems in this moment.

00:59:26.435 --> 00:59:28.560 align:middle line:84%
I'll worry about those
problems tomorrow, whatever.

00:59:28.560 --> 00:59:30.880 align:middle line:90%
I'll resolve them tomorrow.

00:59:30.880 --> 00:59:34.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm really grateful
for my bed right now.

00:59:34.500 --> 00:59:38.670 align:middle line:84%
And we can always be
grateful for something.

00:59:38.670 --> 00:59:40.950 align:middle line:84%
Often, we focus so
much on what's not

00:59:40.950 --> 00:59:43.440 align:middle line:90%
working versus what is working.

00:59:43.440 --> 00:59:45.510 align:middle line:84%
And once you focus
on what is working,

00:59:45.510 --> 00:59:49.380 align:middle line:84%
you'll start noticing that a lot
more is working than it's not.

00:59:49.380 --> 00:59:50.647 align:middle line:90%
And it's all perception.

00:59:50.647 --> 00:59:52.355 align:middle line:84%
I've been on a lot of
humanitarian trips,

00:59:52.355 --> 00:59:57.690 align:middle line:84%
so I've seen, we've pitched
tents in poor villages

00:59:57.690 --> 00:59:59.550 align:middle line:90%
in Guatemala.

00:59:59.550 --> 01:00:01.180 align:middle line:84%
I've traveled to
a lot of places.

01:00:01.180 --> 01:00:02.640 align:middle line:90%
I've seen that.

01:00:02.640 --> 01:00:07.080 align:middle line:84%
I remember we were giving
out all these supplies

01:00:07.080 --> 01:00:09.720 align:middle line:84%
and clothes and things in a
poor village in Nicaragua.

01:00:09.720 --> 01:00:14.820 align:middle line:84%
And I'll never forget,
somehow I dropped something

01:00:14.820 --> 01:00:18.480 align:middle line:84%
and these pencils
fell to the ground.

01:00:18.480 --> 01:00:22.780 align:middle line:84%
And I never saw a bunch
of kids just attack them.

01:00:22.780 --> 01:00:24.150 align:middle line:90%
They just jumped on.

01:00:24.150 --> 01:00:29.340 align:middle line:84%
And I've never seen children
so happy to have a pencil.

01:00:29.340 --> 01:00:30.250 align:middle line:90%
I have a pencil!

01:00:30.250 --> 01:00:33.110 align:middle line:84%
They're running
around, yeah, me, too!

01:00:33.110 --> 01:00:36.030 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, wow.

01:00:36.030 --> 01:00:38.400 align:middle line:90%
It's all relative.

01:00:38.400 --> 01:00:41.520 align:middle line:84%
And so when you've
seen all that,

01:00:41.520 --> 01:00:42.988 align:middle line:84%
it's a lot easier
to be grateful.

01:00:42.988 --> 01:00:45.030 align:middle line:84%
So when I get stuck, and
believe me, to this day,

01:00:45.030 --> 01:00:46.710 align:middle line:84%
I still get stuck
every once in a while

01:00:46.710 --> 01:00:48.880 align:middle line:84%
and I have to do the inner
work and go, here we go again.

01:00:48.880 --> 01:00:50.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm not feeling
good, what's going on

01:00:50.100 --> 01:00:51.475 align:middle line:84%
and what am I
thinking right now.

01:00:51.475 --> 01:00:54.840 align:middle line:84%
And then I, but I can shift it
immediately, because I'm human.

01:00:54.840 --> 01:00:56.333 align:middle line:84%
And so when I need
to be grateful,

01:00:56.333 --> 01:00:57.750 align:middle line:84%
I remember when
my mom passed away

01:00:57.750 --> 01:00:59.820 align:middle line:84%
and I was having a
really difficult time.

01:00:59.820 --> 01:01:03.120 align:middle line:84%
It was shortly after
she passed away.

01:01:03.120 --> 01:01:09.390 align:middle line:84%
And I was sitting in my
backyard feeling sad.

01:01:09.390 --> 01:01:11.760 align:middle line:84%
And then I thought
to myself, now

01:01:11.760 --> 01:01:17.560 align:middle line:84%
is a time to write my
"Fifty Shades of Gratitude."

01:01:17.560 --> 01:01:20.550 align:middle line:84%
And I sat down and I wrote,
and it wasn't easy to write.

01:01:20.550 --> 01:01:23.280 align:middle line:84%
To find 50 things that
you're grateful for?

01:01:23.280 --> 01:01:26.100 align:middle line:84%
It's the first 10 or
12 or 15 are easy.

01:01:26.100 --> 01:01:28.630 align:middle line:84%
I'm happy my
brother's so awesome.

01:01:28.630 --> 01:01:30.600 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy my dad was alive.

01:01:30.600 --> 01:01:32.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy that I can walk.

01:01:32.730 --> 01:01:34.530 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy that the sun is out.

01:01:34.530 --> 01:01:36.060 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy that I'm alive.

01:01:36.060 --> 01:01:37.710 align:middle line:84%
I'm happy that my
dog is healthy.

01:01:37.710 --> 01:01:39.120 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy I have a great team.

01:01:39.120 --> 01:01:39.920 align:middle line:90%
I'm happy.

01:01:39.920 --> 01:01:41.587 align:middle line:84%
And then after a
while, you're like, OK,

01:01:41.587 --> 01:01:45.910 align:middle line:84%
what, and then you start
running out of things.

01:01:45.910 --> 01:01:51.180 align:middle line:84%
And then I realize, I'm
really grateful that I

01:01:51.180 --> 01:01:53.430 align:middle line:90%
had the best mom ever.

01:01:53.430 --> 01:01:58.110 align:middle line:84%
She wasn't the perfect mom, but
she was the perfect mom for me.

01:01:58.110 --> 01:02:01.860 align:middle line:84%
I'm grateful that I had her for
as long as I did in my life.

01:02:01.860 --> 01:02:06.210 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of people lose
their parents at a young age.

01:02:06.210 --> 01:02:10.830 align:middle line:84%
I am so lucky that I've
had both my parents

01:02:10.830 --> 01:02:13.420 align:middle line:90%
for such a long time.

01:02:13.420 --> 01:02:16.100 align:middle line:90%
A lot of people don't get that.

01:02:16.100 --> 01:02:19.700 align:middle line:84%
I am lucky and so
grateful that I had

01:02:19.700 --> 01:02:23.030 align:middle line:90%
a mother that loved me so much.

01:02:23.030 --> 01:02:25.400 align:middle line:84%
There isn't a person on this
planet that loved me more

01:02:25.400 --> 01:02:27.290 align:middle line:90%
than my mother.

01:02:27.290 --> 01:02:28.440 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

01:02:28.440 --> 01:02:29.430 align:middle line:90%
I'm so grateful.

01:02:29.430 --> 01:02:32.180 align:middle line:90%
I'm so lucky.

01:02:32.180 --> 01:02:35.012 align:middle line:84%
Versus like, I can't believe
my mom died and she had cancer

01:02:35.012 --> 01:02:36.970 align:middle line:84%
and she suffered, you
know, all that was going.

01:02:36.970 --> 01:02:38.510 align:middle line:90%
I just shifted it.

01:02:38.510 --> 01:02:42.440 align:middle line:84%
Do you know how quickly
I felt so much better?

01:02:42.440 --> 01:02:43.520 align:middle line:90%
Much better.

01:02:43.520 --> 01:02:46.650 align:middle line:84%
Focus on what's going
right in your life.

01:02:46.650 --> 01:02:49.142 align:middle line:90%
And there's a lot.

01:02:49.142 --> 01:02:51.730 align:middle line:90%
>> That's beautiful, Sonia.

01:02:51.730 --> 01:02:55.460 align:middle line:84%
I want to finish here, if you
can take me from the moment

01:02:55.460 --> 01:02:58.220 align:middle line:84%
that you reached that fifth
step on your stairwell

01:02:58.220 --> 01:03:00.230 align:middle line:84%
and had this epiphany
and this realization,

01:03:00.230 --> 01:03:01.670 align:middle line:84%
and then by the time
you got to the landing

01:03:01.670 --> 01:03:03.920 align:middle line:84%
you had another realization,
to where you are today.

01:03:03.920 --> 01:03:05.510 align:middle line:84%
Because I want to get
closure on this story.

01:03:05.510 --> 01:03:06.927 align:middle line:84%
You've touched on
it a little bit.

01:03:06.927 --> 01:03:10.617 align:middle line:84%
You know, I wrote a book,
I did this, I help people.

01:03:10.617 --> 01:03:12.200 align:middle line:84%
But if we had to go
back to that story

01:03:12.200 --> 01:03:14.392 align:middle line:84%
and you had to fast
forward it and tell me

01:03:14.392 --> 01:03:16.100 align:middle line:84%
what's happened in
your life, what you've

01:03:16.100 --> 01:03:18.183 align:middle line:84%
been able to achieve, the
books you're working on,

01:03:18.183 --> 01:03:22.970 align:middle line:84%
the film that's coming out,
the crystal ball life that you

01:03:22.970 --> 01:03:25.370 align:middle line:84%
looked at and thought, that
would have been impossible,

01:03:25.370 --> 01:03:26.960 align:middle line:90%
but actually became true.

01:03:26.960 --> 01:03:28.730 align:middle line:84%
Can you finish
that story for me?

01:03:28.730 --> 01:03:30.580 align:middle line:84%
I think people would
like to hear it.

01:03:30.580 --> 01:03:31.380 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

01:03:31.380 --> 01:03:33.060 align:middle line:90%
What is she talking about?

01:03:33.060 --> 01:03:33.860 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:03:33.860 --> 01:03:38.360 align:middle line:84%
So my life today is
truly a dream life.

01:03:38.360 --> 01:03:39.270 align:middle line:90%
Is it perfect?

01:03:39.270 --> 01:03:39.770 align:middle line:90%
No.

01:03:39.770 --> 01:03:40.880 align:middle line:90%
I'm like everyone else.

01:03:40.880 --> 01:03:42.770 align:middle line:84%
Like that staircase,
sometimes you go up,

01:03:42.770 --> 01:03:44.390 align:middle line:90%
sometimes you go down.

01:03:44.390 --> 01:03:46.520 align:middle line:84%
And things happen
and life is life.

01:03:46.520 --> 01:03:49.700 align:middle line:84%
Difference is, now
when things happen,

01:03:49.700 --> 01:03:51.890 align:middle line:90%
I allow it to bounce off me.

01:03:51.890 --> 01:03:55.130 align:middle line:84%
I deal with it, I handle it,
I experience it, I feel it

01:03:55.130 --> 01:03:56.660 align:middle line:90%
and I move forward.

01:03:56.660 --> 01:03:59.630 align:middle line:84%
So it's a different
experience altogether.

01:03:59.630 --> 01:04:02.030 align:middle line:84%
So I bounce back really,
really, really quickly whenever

01:04:02.030 --> 01:04:03.270 align:middle line:90%
something happens.

01:04:03.270 --> 01:04:06.470 align:middle line:84%
But my actual life,
I was able to write

01:04:06.470 --> 01:04:09.020 align:middle line:84%
a bestseller book,
